# Git Workflow Rules
- Use short-lived feature branches such as `codex/phase-01-foundation` or `feat/order-flow`.
- Prefer Conventional Commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `refactor:`, `test:`.
- Keep commits scoped and reviewable; do not mix unrelated changes.
- Use explicit phase completion commits such as `chore: complete phase 01 foundation`.
- Never rewrite shared history or force-push without explicit approval.
